     1) Fifteen days after the expiration of the period of use of books and other printed materials, if renewal has not been made, and thirty days if renewal has been made,

 the library staff must send a reminder or notify the reader by mail of the need to return them to the library within ten days.

 If the books and other printed materials are not returned to the library within this period, the library sends a demand to the user for their return or replacement within 10 days with equivalent content and cost.

     2) Users may be deprived of the right to use 'Pocket Library' for a specific or permanent period in the following cases:

- in case of systematic violation of the library's deadlines for returning books without a valid reason;

- in case of deliberate damage to the library's property;

- in case of refusal of the user to compensate for the damage;

- in case of unethical behavior of the user in the library, interfering with the activities of other users and library staff;

- in case of refusal to voluntarily compensate the library for the damage, the user is responsible for the damage caused in accordance with the legislation of the Russian Federation.
